      "source": [
        "# Welcome to the Fear Circuit notebook!\n",
        "#### By the end of this notebook, you will be able to...\n",
        "\n",
        "_1. Understand how our brain learns fear._\n",
        "\n",
        "_2. Recognize what parts of the brain are associated with fear._\n",
        "\n",
        "_3. Examine a 10 cell model learning and forgetting its fear of a noise!_\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "Instructions: To run a code block, click on it to __select__ it, and then press __SHIFT__ and __ENTER__ or click the __PLAY__ arrow in the top left corner of the block. Note that you do __not__ need to understand Python to use this notebook--just run each code cell and observe the plots that follow it.\n",
        "\n",
        "To begin the notebook, press the \"Reset file name\" button. This lesson comes with two EEG example files: __EEG_Example1__ and __EEG_Example2__. Select the  file you would like to use, then run each code block that follows.\n",
        "\n",
        "---"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "Next we can run the simulation, our setup here is to teach the model to fear a tone by combining the tone with a shock so that they become associated. \n",
        "Each tone will last 500 ms\n",
        "Each shock will last 100 ms\n",
        "\n",
        "Phases:\n",
        "Sensitization phase:\n",
        "  10 unpaired tones and shocks with shocks occuring randomly in the tones\n",
        "\n",
        "Conditioning phase:\n",
        "- 10 paired tones and shocks (tone for first 400 ms in last 100 ms both tone and shock start)\n",
        "\n",
        "40 seconds after conditioning extinction begins\n",
        "\n",
        "First extinction phases:\n",
        "- 30 tones given with no shock (so 30 trials with 4000 ms delays between the trials)\n",
        "\n",
        "Second extinction phase:\n",
        "- Another 30 pure tones\n",
        "\n",
        "Finally, we will test the model for some kind of spontaneous recovery of fear after a delay of 840 seconds.\n",
        "\n",
        "Entire experiment will last 1200 seconds. "
      ]
    },

        "%matplotlib inline\n",
        "from bmtk.analyzer.spike_trains import to_dataframe\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",

        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import math\n",
        "\n",
        "df = to_dataframe(config_file='simulation_config.json')\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",

        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "node_spike_array = []\n",
        "def create_arrays(node_spike_array):\n",
        "    node_num = 0\n",

        "    while(node_num <= 9):\n",
        "        df0 = df.loc[df['node_ids'] == node_num]\n",
        "\n",
        "        x0 = df0['timestamps'].tolist()\n",
        "        first_trial = []\n",
        "        second_trial = []\n",
        "        third_trial = []\n",
        "        fourth_trial = []\n",
        "        fifth_trial = []\n",
        "        sixth_trial = []\n",
        "        seventh_trial = []\n",
        "        eighth_trial = []\n",
        "        ninth_trial = []\n",
        "        tenth_trial = []\n",
        "\n",
        "        for i in range(len(x0)):\n",
        "            if (x0[i] >= 0 and x0[i] <= 400):\n",
        "                first_trial.append(x0[i])\n",
        "            if (x0[i] >= 4000 and x0[i] <= 4400):\n",
        "                second_trial.append(x0[i])\n",
        "            if (x0[i] >= 8000 and x0[i] <= 8400):\n",
        "                third_trial.append(x0[i])\n",
        "            if (x0[i] >= 12000 and x0[i] <= 12400):\n",
        "                fourth_trial.append(x0[i])\n",
        "            if (x0[i] >= 16000 and x0[i] <= 16400):\n",
        "                fifth_trial.append(x0[i])\n",
        "            if (x0[i] >= 20000 and x0[i] <= 20400):\n",
        "                sixth_trial.append(x0[i])\n",
        "            if (x0[i] >= 24000 and x0[i] <= 24400):\n",
        "                seventh_trial.append(x0[i])\n",
        "            if (x0[i] >= 28000 and x0[i] <= 28400):\n",
        "                eighth_trial.append(x0[i])\n",
        "            if (x0[i] >= 32000 and x0[i] <= 32400):\n",
        "                ninth_trial.append(x0[i])\n",
        "            if (x0[i] >= 36000 and x0[i] <= 36400):\n",
        "                tenth_trial.append(x0[i])\n",
        "\n",
        "        for i in range(len(second_trial)):\n",
        "            second_trial[i] -= 4000\n",
        "        for i in range(len(third_trial)):\n",
        "            third_trial[i] -= 8000\n",
        "        for i in range(len(fourth_trial)):\n",
        "            fourth_trial[i] -= 12000\n",
        "        for i in range(len(fifth_trial)):\n",
        "            fifth_trial[i] -= 16000\n",
        "        for i in range(len(sixth_trial)):\n",
        "            sixth_trial[i] -= 20000\n",
        "        for i in range(len(seventh_trial)):\n",
        "            seventh_trial[i] -= 24000\n",
        "        for i in range(len(eighth_trial)):\n",
        "            eighth_trial[i] -= 28000\n",
        "        for i in range(len(ninth_trial)):\n",
        "            ninth_trial[i] -= 32000\n",
        "        for i in range(len(tenth_trial)):\n",
        "            tenth_trial[i] -= 36000\n",
        "\n",
        "        final_array = np.concatenate((first_trial, second_trial, third_trial, fourth_trial,\n",
        "                                      fifth_trial, sixth_trial, seventh_trial, eighth_trial,\n",
        "                                      ninth_trial, tenth_trial))\n",
        "\n",
        "        node_spike_array.append(final_array)\n",
        "\n",
        "        node_num = node_num+1\n",
        "\n",
        "def find_bins(array, width):\n",
        "    minimmum = np.min(array)\n",
        "    maximmum = np.max(array)\n",
        "    bound_min = -1.0 * (minimmum % width - minimmum)\n",
        "    bound_max = maximmum - maximmum % width + width\n",
        "    n = int((bound_max - bound_min) / width) + 1\n",
        "    bins = np.linspace(bound_min, bound_max, n)\n",
        "    return bins\n",
        "\n",
        "create_arrays(node_spike_array)\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, axs = plt.subplots(3, 3, sharey=True, tight_layout=True, sharex=True)\n",

        "\n",
        "\n",
        "i = 0\n",
        "column_cnt = 0\n",
        "row_cnt = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "while(i < 9):\n",
        "    bins = find_bins(node_spike_array[i], 10)\n",
        "\n",
        "    axs[row_cnt, column_cnt].hist(x=node_spike_array[i], bins=bins)\n",
        "    axs[row_cnt, column_cnt].set_title('pyramidal ' + str(i+1))\n",
        "    if(i == 8):\n",
        "        axs[row_cnt, column_cnt].set_title('Interneuron 1 ')\n",
        "    # axs[row_cnt, column_cnt].ylabel(\"spikes\")\n",
        "    # axs[row_cnt, column_cnt].xlabel('ms')\n",
        "\n",
        "    axs[row_cnt, column_cnt].set_xlim([0,400])\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "    column_cnt = column_cnt+1\n",
        "    if(column_cnt > 2):\n",
        "        column_cnt = 0\n",
        "        row_cnt = row_cnt+1\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "    i = i+1\n",
        "\n",
        "for ax in axs.flat:\n",
        "    ax.set(xlabel='time(ms)', ylabel='# of spikes')\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = [12,6]\n",
        "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 150\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
